INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('07e81a1181e09','2024-01-10 21:44:49.419','2024-01-10 21:44:49.419','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,'- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1a34e88a91cbc','2024-01-10 21:44:49.161','2024-01-10 21:44:49.161','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,'- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it\''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1cc0f4d7ce4db','2024-01-10 21:44:49.608','2024-01-10 21:44:49.608','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,'- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1ea8bc0957841','2024-01-10 21:44:49.123','2024-01-10 21:44:49.123','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,'- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('23bd2cdf354f7','2024-01-10 21:44:49.080','2024-01-10 21:44:49.080','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,'\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('2c13f96c0b759','2024-01-10 21:44:49.284','2024-01-10 21:44:49.284','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,'- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('39be5fd7ca5f','2024-01-10 21:44:49.104','2024-01-10 21:44:49.104','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,'- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('41d49ecd84dd3','2024-01-10 21:44:49.142','2024-01-10 21:44:49.142','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,'- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it\''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4d858f53faea5','2024-01-10 21:44:49.485','2024-01-10 21:44:49.485','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,'\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('53e2344555fa','2024-01-10 21:44:49.244','2024-01-10 21:44:49.244','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,'- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('582212eb83f05','2024-02-11 19:06:32.356','2024-02-11 19:06:32.356','Tejfölös zöldbableves',1,'4',0,0,'- 120 g paprikás kolbász\n- 1 fej vöröshagyma (130 g/fej)\n- 2 gerezd fokhagyma\n- só, bors\n- 1 tk füstölt fűszerpaprika\n- 2 db babérlevél\n- 80 g sárgarépa\n- 200 g krumpli\n- 1 ½ liter alaplé\n- 400 g fagyasztott zöldbab\n- 1 tk almaecet\n- 1 tk keményítő\n- 4 ek tejföl\n- 1 csokor friss petrezselyem','1. A kolbászt kis kockákra vágjuk és közepes lángon elkezdjük lepirítani egy lábasban. A zsír nagy részét leszedjük róla, majd belerakjuk az apróra vágott hagymát és fokhagymát, és sózzuk, borsozzuk.\n2. Rárakjuk a paprikát, a babérlevelet, a kis kockákra vágott répát és krumplit, majd felöntjük az alaplével. Hagyjuk, hogy félig megpuhuljanak a zöldségek, majd mehet bele a zöldbab is. \n3. Miután újraforrt, 4-5 percig még főzzük és beletesszük az ecetet.\n4. A tejfölt kikeverjük a keményítővel és hozzákeverünk egy kis forró levest is, majd az egészet folyamatos kevergetés mellett a leveshez öntjük. Hagyjuk 1-2 percet főni, megszórjuk apróra vágott friss petrezselyemmel és meg is vagyunk.','','soup','t9gei4hpxhopx5mckcjx.jpg','cookbook/demo/multiacc001/t9gei4hpxhopx5mckcjx','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5ddf174a9c768','2024-02-11 19:09:23.970','2024-02-11 19:09:23.970','Currys cukkinikrémleves',1,'6',0,0,'- 600 g cukkini\n- 20 ml olívaolaj\n- 1 fej vöröshagyma (130 g/fej)\n- 200 g burgonya\n- 4 gerezd fokhagyma\n- 2 ek sárga currypaszta\n- 350 ml konzerv kókusztejszín\n- 1 l zöldségalaplé\n- só, bors\n- ½ csokor menta\n- ½ csokor petrezselyem\n- 1 db citrom leve','1. A leveshez felaprítjuk a vöröshagymát, és egy fazékban, közepes lángon lepirítjuk az olívaolajon. Mehetnek rá az egész fokhagymagerezdek, a felkockázott cukkini és burgonya, majd magasabb lángra kapcsolunk, és alaposan lepirítjuk a zöldségeket.\n2. Ekkor hozzáadjuk a currypasztát, felöntjük a zöldségalaplével, és közepes lángon 18-20 perc alatt puhára főzzük a zöldségeket. \n3. Mikor megpuhultak a zöldségek, hozzáadjuk a zöldfűszerek háromnegyedét, egy keveset finomra aprítva meghagyunk a tálaláshoz. Mehet hozzá egy citrom frissen facsart leve is, majd botmixerrel krémesre turmixoljuk a levest.\n4. Két merőkanálnyit kiveszünk belőle egy tálba, hozzáadjuk a kókuszkrémet, elkeverjük, majd fokozatosan hozzáöntjük a leveshez. Alacsony lángon 2-3 percet főzzük még, majd friss fűszernövényekkel és a sajtropogóssal tálaljuk.','','soup','utul1ajcxzgr9egalh2v.jpg','cookbook/demo/multiacc001/utul1ajcxzgr9egalh2v','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5fc3138d4d99b','2024-02-11 19:27:34.679','2024-02-11 19:27:34.679','Madras curry',2,'4',0,0,'- 600g csirkemell/csirkecomb filé\n- 1 kisebb fej vöröshagyma\n- 2-4 gerezd fokhagyma\n- 1 nagyujjnyi gyömbér\n- 3 púpozott teáskanál Madras curry fűszerkeverék\n- 1 doboz paradicsomkonzerv\n- 3 dl kókusztej (sűrű, krémes)','1. A csirkét megtisztítjuk és felkockázzuk.\n2. A hagymát felaprítjuk, kevés olajon egy edényben üvegesre pároljuk.\n3. Hozzá reszeljüka gyömbért, megkevergetjük, majd hozzáadjuk a csirkét is, pirítjuk fehéredésig.\n4. Fűszerezzük sóval és a madras curry fűszerrel, pirítjuk tovább pár percig.\n5. Hozzáöntjük a paradicsomot, kis lángon főzzük 30 percet. \n6. Hozzáadjuk a kókusztejet és felforraljuk.\n\nTálalhatjuk naan kenyérrel vagy rizzsel.','','main dish','wivq5czaqffkea6vs6i1.jpg','cookbook/demo/multiacc001/wivq5czaqffkea6vs6i1','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('82d021b260f4','2024-01-10 21:44:49.179','2024-01-10 21:44:49.179','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,'- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('87c3043e4f02a','2024-01-10 21:44:49.199','2024-01-10 21:44:49.199','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,'- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9346e3b780078','2024-01-10 21:44:49.586','2024-01-10 21:44:49.586','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,'- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it\''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9def1ab3038cd','2024-02-25 15:52:35.310','2024-02-25 15:52:35.310','Indiai vajas csirke',2,'4',60,40,'__Marinált hús__\n- 800 g csirkemellfilé\n- 140 ml natúr joghurt\n- 3 gerezd reszelt fokhagyma\n- 3 cm friss reszelt gyömbér\n- 3 tk garam masala\n- 2 tk kurkuma\n- 2 tk fahéj\n- 2 tk chilipor\n- só, bors\n\n__Szósz__\n- 4 ek vaj\n- 1 fej vöröshagyma\n- 2 gerezd fokhagyma\n- 400 g aprított paradicsomkonzerv\n- butter chicken paszta/fűszerkeverék\n- 1 tk koriander\n- 250 ml kókusztejszín\n- só, bors\n- fél lime leve','1. Az indiai vajas csirke elkészítéséhez a csirkét megtisztítjuk, 3 cm-es kockákra vágjuk és egy tálba dobjuk. Hozzáadjuk a marinád többi hozzávalóját, belemasszírozzuk a húsba, és a hűtőbe rakjuk pihenni legalább egy órára.\n2. Az alaphoz a vajon lepirítjuk a felaprított vöröshagymát, fokhagymát, friss chilit és a reszelt gyömbért. Alaposan pirítsuk le, a vaj kissé megbarnulhat.\n3. Ezután beleborítjuk a pácolt csirkét és alaposan lepirítjuk kb. 5 perc alatt.\n4.  Felöntjük az aprított paradicsommal, beleküldjük a fűszereket és fedő alatt 10 percet rotyogtatjuk.\n5.  Ekkor folyamatos kevergetés mellett hozzáöntjük a kókusztejszínt is, és további 5-6 percig főzzük.\n6.  A végén hozzáadjuk a lime levét.','https://streetkitchen.hu/azsiai-etelek/indiai-vajas-csirke-2/','main dish','bhyyoqiz7bhwaok3hswj.jpg','cookbook/demo/multiacc001/bhyyoqiz7bhwaok3hswj','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ace7ce05e5084','2024-01-10 21:44:49.520','2024-01-10 21:44:49.520','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,'- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('bdc198e241029','2024-01-10 21:44:49.009','2024-01-10 21:44:49.009','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,'- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it\''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don\''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c9f43ad93b53b','2024-01-10 21:44:49.264','2024-01-10 21:44:49.264','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,'- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn\''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d04c6bdcbb799','2024-01-10 21:44:49.386','2024-01-10 21:44:49.386','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,'- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn\''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('df64862404af9','2024-01-10T21:44:49.359+00:00','2024-01-10T21:44:49.359+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'14 cupcakes',15,20,'- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e1754e0925fe8','2024-01-10 21:44:49.304','2024-01-10 21:44:49.304','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,'- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e39092686910e','2024-01-10 21:44:49.449','2024-01-10 21:44:49.449','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,'\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e4610a0a06778','2024-01-10 21:44:49.564','2024-01-10 21:44:49.564','Banana pancakes',1,'12 pancakes',10,30,'- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f1e635aec6f11','2024-01-10 21:44:49.060','2024-01-10 21:44:49.060','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,'- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f68bf5e731a58','2024-01-10 21:44:49.222','2024-01-10 21:44:49.222','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,'- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('8bab4ab5eb448','2024-06-12T20:26:31.197+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:31.197+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('a94256e103c6c','2024-06-12T20:26:31.548+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:31.548+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1c47047d5c12e','2024-06-12T20:26:31.738+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:31.738+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('cde6c4f1c799d','2024-06-12T20:26:31.897+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:31.897+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('8050eea3e28d9','2024-06-12T20:26:32.065+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:32.065+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c79071144cfb7','2024-06-12T20:26:32.220+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:32.220+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1fd2d0b024d9a','2024-06-12T20:26:32.384+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:32.384+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f8d2e64120578','2024-06-12T20:26:32.566+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:32.566+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4c3c4d5678103','2024-06-12T20:26:32.716+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:32.716+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('50bb47c8ab6d7','2024-06-12T20:26:32.864+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:32.864+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('7a3c60cd76c8','2024-06-12T20:26:33.038+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:33.038+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4c817acc0c912','2024-06-12T20:26:33.287+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:33.287+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ef2391b33d21f','2024-06-12T20:26:33.457+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:33.457+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('7350f5a1e49e6','2024-06-12T20:26:33.623+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:33.623+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('cb61a6ae25193','2024-06-12T20:26:34.259+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:34.259+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('252d713a38fc3','2024-06-12T20:26:34.621+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:34.621+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('83bd52dbe3e4c','2024-06-12T20:26:34.914+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:34.914+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d188b4ee3188c','2024-06-12T20:26:35.160+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:35.160+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f868e954ba4c9','2024-06-12T20:26:35.574+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:35.574+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('8431eb5ba3445','2024-06-12T20:26:35.980+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:35.980+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('a9b505abd8735','2024-06-12T20:26:36.436+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:36.436+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('b5618531cafa5','2024-06-12T20:26:36.584+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:36.584+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c087cdb8a686c','2024-06-12T20:26:36.732+00:00','2024-06-12T20:26:36.732+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','2b93dc98ab36f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('07e173cceb0fb','2024-06-12T20:33:40.413+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:40.413+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('08279fbef45cb','2024-06-12T20:33:40.714+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:40.714+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('927d953b76fd5','2024-06-12T20:33:40.856+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:40.856+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f337c6d2db02b','2024-06-12T20:33:41.002+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:41.002+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4501b84897b67','2024-06-12T20:33:41.145+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:41.145+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ca63acf8ab12d','2024-06-12T20:33:41.294+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:41.294+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('80ad781f9e565','2024-06-12T20:33:41.443+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:41.443+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('358e54fe814ab','2024-06-12T20:33:41.599+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:41.599+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('45a46de10e373','2024-06-12T20:33:41.744+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:41.744+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('3e03f49c53eb','2024-06-12T20:33:41.885+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:41.885+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4eb55c6a25f19','2024-06-12T20:33:42.048+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:42.048+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9d70d9db8c92c','2024-06-12T20:33:42.197+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:42.197+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('230bdbe19c6f2','2024-06-12T20:33:42.343+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:42.343+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('100d1b5cec8ca','2024-06-12T20:33:42.478+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:42.478+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('bb27051043b85','2024-06-12T20:33:43.122+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:43.122+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d5084cfc440e1','2024-06-12T20:33:43.390+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:43.390+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('8963dfce9942','2024-06-12T20:33:43.706+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:43.706+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9cf8e98126a94','2024-06-12T20:33:43.955+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:43.955+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('aef9fd76c583a','2024-06-12T20:33:44.346+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:44.346+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('2ba410334a3bd','2024-06-12T20:33:44.753+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:44.753+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5ebdc9b7c0cca','2024-06-12T20:33:45.195+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:45.195+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('47fea665ce8af','2024-06-12T20:33:45.338+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:45.338+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1001cc12855ee','2024-06-12T20:33:45.478+00:00','2024-06-12T20:33:45.478+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','200433b5cb87f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('91ac059ce88d3','2024-06-12T20:57:02.338+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:02.338+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('a9c70b1975d61','2024-06-12T20:57:02.625+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:02.625+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('421cb8f4ef54d','2024-06-12T20:57:02.750+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:02.750+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c3ead45062248','2024-06-12T20:57:02.897+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:02.897+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('087595130772f','2024-06-12T20:57:03.025+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:03.025+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9ee9deaaedf44','2024-06-12T20:57:03.149+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:03.149+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('b2390c494a193','2024-06-12T20:57:03.270+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:03.270+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('0c10ba4180fdc','2024-06-12T20:57:03.391+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:03.391+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4d0c8be64ac5f','2024-06-12T20:57:03.517+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:03.517+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('3dd552f992878','2024-06-12T20:57:03.648+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:03.648+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f7eaf50e6628e','2024-06-12T20:57:03.775+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:03.775+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('95557ebed578d','2024-06-12T20:57:03.900+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:03.900+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('a7a2cf8a3aea8','2024-06-12T20:57:04.024+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:04.024+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('b6c221086b12d','2024-06-12T20:57:04.163+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:04.163+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('eb3c59f4b97fd','2024-06-12T20:57:04.690+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:04.690+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ba2ba5cfabe7e','2024-06-12T20:57:04.933+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:04.933+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('8248cba6be3e7','2024-06-12T20:57:05.144+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:05.144+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('dee5d9cd0d576','2024-06-12T20:57:05.356+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:05.356+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d14b711bcc9a2','2024-06-12T20:57:05.688+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:05.688+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('6e54eac3f48be','2024-06-12T20:57:06.020+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:06.020+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('cf52c2e09a0d5','2024-06-12T20:57:06.405+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:06.405+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1b718774efffc','2024-06-12T20:57:06.526+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:06.526+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('a0e6c6e98bd2d','2024-06-12T20:57:06.649+00:00','2024-06-12T20:57:06.649+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','d7ca1a2f9ac4d');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9c9f88259c448','2024-06-12T20:58:23.714+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:23.714+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d4ca1b7b0022d','2024-06-12T20:58:23.971+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:23.971+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e511975a88403','2024-06-12T20:58:24.098+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:24.098+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('26de6a2e0bfdb','2024-06-12T20:58:24.223+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:24.223+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('136729a1516a7','2024-06-12T20:58:24.349+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:24.349+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('119622485ef63','2024-06-12T20:58:24.472+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:24.472+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c305a583e95e2','2024-06-12T20:58:24.596+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:24.596+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('876522abed983','2024-06-12T20:58:24.720+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:24.720+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('444eac005c127','2024-06-12T20:58:24.846+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:24.846+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ee6db45a8cb6e','2024-06-12T20:58:24.974+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:24.974+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('6c56358ceaf1f','2024-06-12T20:58:25.120+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:25.120+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('642791cc38a23','2024-06-12T20:58:25.244+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:25.244+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f51163fac1873','2024-06-12T20:58:25.409+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:25.409+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('b95ca050d4358','2024-06-12T20:58:25.544+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:25.544+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('63eec05f464bf','2024-06-12T20:58:26.053+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:26.053+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('2b7df9e39fe95','2024-06-12T20:58:26.295+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:26.295+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('7069cc71f5a31','2024-06-12T20:58:26.504+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:26.504+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('807485b6c13b6','2024-06-12T20:58:26.714+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:26.714+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('77e0570ffacdc','2024-06-12T20:58:27.044+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:27.044+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('48b1437e4bd42','2024-06-12T20:58:27.370+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:27.370+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f567dd946dacb','2024-06-12T20:58:27.731+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:27.731+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('deb908c6df91f','2024-06-12T20:58:27.853+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:27.853+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ffd0dda81c3a4','2024-06-12T20:58:27.974+00:00','2024-06-12T20:58:27.974+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','d511bc4520e6c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('283c934a864d','2024-06-12T20:59:00.028+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:00.028+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('2c93730d7d33d','2024-06-12T20:59:00.289+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:00.289+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e909f5db4c2f8','2024-06-12T20:59:00.415+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:00.415+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('bffe5cf4c971a','2024-06-12T20:59:00.541+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:00.541+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('59cd381e7574c','2024-06-12T20:59:00.665+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:00.665+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('65e24b07a2b9c','2024-06-12T20:59:00.790+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:00.790+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('a7774736b0544','2024-06-12T20:59:00.916+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:00.916+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('3657e7e985157','2024-06-12T20:59:01.041+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:01.041+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d96b64909719a','2024-06-12T20:59:01.166+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:01.166+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('dc24ea66303d6','2024-06-12T20:59:01.298+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:01.298+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('6fbd9ad5e42d6','2024-06-12T20:59:01.421+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:01.421+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('3b2f4b116cc4e','2024-06-12T20:59:01.546+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:01.546+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('20e386e8e2fad','2024-06-12T20:59:01.686+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:01.686+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('0b7caa2160d46','2024-06-12T20:59:01.838+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:01.838+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('3d6c3a2de6065','2024-06-12T20:59:02.359+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:02.359+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('edc127b7a3597','2024-06-12T20:59:02.604+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:02.604+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('6b6343779c6d','2024-06-12T20:59:02.817+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:02.817+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('14b1b72427215','2024-06-12T20:59:03.032+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:03.032+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('3bd67488097e6','2024-06-12T20:59:03.371+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:03.371+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('8552b1546aca8','2024-06-12T20:59:03.713+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:03.713+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('2267b939c647','2024-06-12T20:59:04.089+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:04.089+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('598555fd601c','2024-06-12T20:59:04.213+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:04.213+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('02329ef3a09fa','2024-06-12T20:59:04.336+00:00','2024-06-12T20:59:04.336+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','d7b08ac65cf1f');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('371f3c9ccb15c','2024-06-13T06:31:42.040+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:42.040+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ae9276ae698d1','2024-06-13T06:31:42.291+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:42.291+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5947f38195eab','2024-06-13T06:31:42.416+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:42.416+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('279887a09af2e','2024-06-13T06:31:42.542+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:42.542+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('580f864da19a1','2024-06-13T06:31:42.666+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:42.666+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('2b7e76a9d2913','2024-06-13T06:31:42.793+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:42.793+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('b2035782e53da','2024-06-13T06:31:42.914+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:42.914+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('3b0b7f44ec25f','2024-06-13T06:31:43.058+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:43.058+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d0241cb258e1f','2024-06-13T06:31:43.180+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:43.180+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ade8a28d8f69b','2024-06-13T06:31:43.308+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:43.308+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('62d7ec3e36d99','2024-06-13T06:31:43.437+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:43.437+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('0fbb418108d16','2024-06-13T06:31:43.567+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:43.567+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9f3cb5e4a05dd','2024-06-13T06:31:43.693+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:43.693+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d4f3ec88e8a11','2024-06-13T06:31:43.820+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:43.820+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('36d9d0fa2d588','2024-06-13T06:31:44.348+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:44.348+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('74de112de8b88','2024-06-13T06:31:44.590+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:44.590+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('15b520af6580c','2024-06-13T06:31:44.804+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:44.804+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ae5d359e6c695','2024-06-13T06:31:45.020+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:45.020+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('273c2139a8d3a','2024-06-13T06:31:45.361+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:45.361+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('fc52ceea673de','2024-06-13T06:31:45.689+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:45.689+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('faa0ba439c703','2024-06-13T06:31:46.057+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:46.057+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ee8c3dd0fc947','2024-06-13T06:31:46.178+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:46.178+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d58e578345b47','2024-06-13T06:31:46.301+00:00','2024-06-13T06:31:46.301+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','4bcf16eccb212');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5c3c938857b74','2024-06-14T16:22:59.209+00:00','2024-06-14T16:22:59.209+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('089c1732e5edb','2024-06-14T16:22:59.715+00:00','2024-06-14T16:22:59.715+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f61f3b457f2b5','2024-06-14T16:22:59.843+00:00','2024-06-14T16:22:59.843+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('02e755f8c80de','2024-06-14T16:22:59.969+00:00','2024-06-14T16:22:59.969+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('44045d61f8934','2024-06-14T16:23:00.093+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:00.093+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f160516f06f52','2024-06-14T16:23:00.216+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:00.216+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('695b8fb87fb27','2024-06-14T16:23:00.345+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:00.345+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c03eb4b00a4cc','2024-06-14T16:23:00.469+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:00.469+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d2bee4f7b716f','2024-06-14T16:23:00.626+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:00.626+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('2d60647fc07a9','2024-06-14T16:23:00.752+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:00.752+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9cd09ec61cc35','2024-06-14T16:23:00.874+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:00.874+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('dae33cd6a73d2','2024-06-14T16:23:00.996+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:00.996+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('71e4966fae2ea','2024-06-14T16:23:01.119+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:01.119+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('6f77ed88e0255','2024-06-14T16:23:01.244+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:01.244+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c6bde1b05d2a','2024-06-14T16:23:01.753+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:01.753+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('969d187eae812','2024-06-14T16:23:02.003+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:02.003+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('862419ac0990a','2024-06-14T16:23:02.215+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:02.215+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('ca2669b53ec03','2024-06-14T16:23:02.428+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:02.428+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('b67079f4e45fb','2024-06-14T16:23:02.758+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:02.758+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c8f63f6940225','2024-06-14T16:23:03.086+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:03.086+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('92d07bd8ac046','2024-06-14T16:23:03.448+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:03.448+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('6409d47c5f7bf','2024-06-14T16:23:03.571+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:03.571+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1de0a5d672e2','2024-06-14T16:23:03.691+00:00','2024-06-14T16:23:03.691+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','d8d707ecb5129');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5aea273174d5d','2024-06-23T06:51:25.598+00:00','2024-06-23T06:51:25.598+00:00','Test recipe',2,'3',0,0,replace('- ingr 1\n- ingr 2','\n',char(10)),replace('1. step\n2. step\n3. step','\n',char(10)),'','soup','vemowjhbs90sribij28c.jpg','cookbook/demo/multiacc001/vemowjhbs90sribij28c','multiacc001');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('edb6e78e0934b','2024-06-23T12:47:22.940+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:22.940+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('d588d0aa002c6','2024-06-23T12:47:23.199+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:23.199+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4e42feecf9abc','2024-06-23T12:47:23.325+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:23.325+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4e4bd3ab03603','2024-06-23T12:47:23.451+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:23.451+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('71fae6e3e7976','2024-06-23T12:47:23.579+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:23.579+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4248aefbf308e','2024-06-23T12:47:23.709+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:23.709+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e3637fa1a25ce','2024-06-23T12:47:23.834+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:23.834+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4a4339d6d1704','2024-06-23T12:47:23.959+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:23.959+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('db215ee402982','2024-06-23T12:47:24.085+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:24.085+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1c109d1ae5655','2024-06-23T12:47:24.213+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:24.213+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5f7bd53094eaa','2024-06-23T12:47:24.352+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:24.352+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('283f36d6a8beb','2024-06-23T12:47:24.498+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:24.498+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f17c470c713e8','2024-06-23T12:47:24.631+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:24.631+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e548847817327','2024-06-23T12:47:24.763+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:24.763+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('2c95ca7142064','2024-06-23T12:47:25.319+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:25.319+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('889b72828cb0d','2024-06-23T12:47:25.562+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:25.562+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('90f52a69f7817','2024-06-23T12:47:25.775+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:25.775+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('a7c6577f5007','2024-06-23T12:47:25.989+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:25.989+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('533786c809c0d','2024-06-23T12:47:26.322+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:26.322+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e900ce3be2cbc','2024-06-23T12:47:26.663+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:26.663+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('33843d1366518','2024-06-23T12:47:27.032+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:27.032+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('6d010d6f0b261','2024-06-23T12:47:27.153+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:27.153+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4ac30c288c261','2024-06-23T12:47:27.281+00:00','2024-06-23T12:47:27.281+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','9e0c32c0e1338');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5de718d3ecbd2','2024-06-23T12:49:16.514+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:16.514+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('907421fd5685e','2024-06-23T12:49:16.782+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:16.782+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('6232375f42d13','2024-06-23T12:49:16.934+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:16.934+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('49c4a5770595d','2024-06-23T12:49:17.069+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:17.069+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('8bfdc140168d','2024-06-23T12:49:17.200+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:17.200+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('48b673151eec3','2024-06-23T12:49:17.329+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:17.329+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('147415ae7f8c9','2024-06-23T12:49:17.459+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:17.459+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('aae90dec568a6','2024-06-23T12:49:17.586+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:17.586+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('8a842c6832d69','2024-06-23T12:49:17.712+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:17.712+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('1bf57e77309fc','2024-06-23T12:49:17.846+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:17.846+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('5c44799a6ac67','2024-06-23T12:49:17.973+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:17.973+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('fa6b0f7bb456b','2024-06-23T12:49:18.108+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:18.108+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9e133e7078377','2024-06-23T12:49:18.233+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:18.233+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('729e102dcc267','2024-06-23T12:49:18.361+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:18.361+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('58e95368c816d','2024-06-23T12:49:18.905+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:18.905+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('13623e722ad03','2024-06-23T12:49:19.231+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:19.231+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('08465a879a24b','2024-06-23T12:49:19.468+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:19.468+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9070c116a950e','2024-06-23T12:49:19.705+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:19.705+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('81701e328d933','2024-06-23T12:49:20.070+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:20.070+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('45bb94a976865','2024-06-23T12:49:20.446+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:20.446+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('4d0aeb138207f','2024-06-23T12:49:20.851+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:20.851+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('08b7da000d43e','2024-06-23T12:49:20.977+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:20.977+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e1b079481ad5','2024-06-23T12:49:21.108+00:00','2024-06-23T12:49:21.108+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','664e906be2d6a');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('3dc90e57a934b','2024-06-23T12:55:06.849+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:06.849+00:00','Spagetti bolognese sauce',0,'4-5 servings',10,50,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 500 g italian tomato sauce\n- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 tbsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 1 tsp salt\n- pepper\n- chilli powder, to taste\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Increase the heat to medium-high, add minced meat and cook until browned.\n3. Stir in tomato sauce, finely chopped garlic, season with salt, sugar, chilli and pepper. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, with lid slightly open. Cook for 40 minutes.\n4. Add oregano to the sauce, cook for 10 more minutes and it''s all done.\n5. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta according to package instructions; drain well.\n6. Serve with pasta and don''t forget to put a lot of shredded gouda cheese on top.','\n',char(10)),'','sauce','emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','cookbook/default/emanuel-ekstrom-_CO7YZ501g4-unsplash_qgrwri.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9b8be2934d2f9','2024-06-23T12:55:07.117+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:07.117+00:00','Apple pie',0,'12 pieces',20,25,replace('- 300 g flour\n- 100 g soft butter\n- 100 g sugar\n- 2 egg yolk\n- half pack of baking powder\n- milk (enough to knead the dough)\n- 1 kg apple, peeled, cored and shredded\n- cinnamon and sugar, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a mixing bowl add the flour, soft butter, sugar, egg yolk, baking powder and mix them together.\n2. Add milk until the dough can be kneaded.\n3. Divide the dough into two pieces.\n4. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n5. Sprinkle the work surface with flour and roll out bottom pie crust to circle. Wrap it around your rolling pin to transfer it to the pie plate.\n6. Add shredded apple as a next layer, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.\n7. Roll out second crust to a circle and place it on top of the apple layer. Poke the crust with a fork.\n8. Bake the pie for 25 minutes.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','cookbook/default/didi-miam-0lqRhBh0I40-unsplash_rgerci.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('cf6efed258822','2024-06-23T12:55:07.255+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:07.255+00:00','Super soft crescent rolls',0,'10 crescent rolls',15,100,replace('\n- 310 ml milk\n- 30 g fresh yeast\n- 25 g sugar\n- 500 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 30 g soft butter','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine warm milk, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt, butter and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 40-60 minutes, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 10 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls, roll out into a triangle shape. Than roll the triangle, starting at the wide end and tucking the pointy end under the roll. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each roll. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','cookbook/default/29gR4Pax-vajas-kifli.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('dc7c3f1132122','2024-06-23T12:55:07.394+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:07.394+00:00','Sandwich bun',0,'8 buns',15,100,replace('- 210 ml water\n- 8 g fresh yeast\n- 1 tbsp sugar\n- 400 g flour\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 egg\n- 1 tbsp oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine 50 ml warm water, sugar and the yeast. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes to activate the yeast.\n2. In a mixing bowl add flour, salt and the egg, add the rest of the water (160 ml), oil and the yeast mixture.\n3. Mix until the dough is formed.\n4. Knead by hand on a lightly floured surface or with the dough hook attachment of the stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. (this take about 10 minutes)\n5. Grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer the dough to the greased bowl. Cover it with kitchen towel, preventing it from drying out. Let the dough rise for about 1 hour, or until it has doubled in size.\n6. Cut the dough into 8 portions. Shape the dough into tight balls. Place them on a baking sheet.\n7. Let the dough rise again for 20 minutes. Cover them with kitchen towel.\n8. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n9. Whisk the egg and water to make the egg wash. Lightly brush the egg wash over each bun. Sprinkle with the seeds to taste.\n10. Bake the sandwich rolls for 16 to 20 minutes, or until the buns are golden brown.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','cookbook/default/laura-filip-W0PDHT_sYoQ-unsplash_b49wz9.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('7e8e58db39214','2024-06-23T12:55:07.532+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:07.532+00:00','Meatballs',0,'12 balls',15,40,replace('- 500 g minced beef/pork\n- 1 egg\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- 60 g dried breadcrumbs (or panko crumbs)\n- fresh parsley','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the minced meat, egg, spices and chopped parsley together.\n2. With wet hands make balls from the mixture.\n3. Preheat the oven to 200 Celsius.\n4. Cover the balls with dried breadcrumbs, place them on a baking sheet.\n5. Bake the meatballs for 40 minutes, turn them 2-3 times. The meatballs should all be evenly cooked and nicely browned on the outside.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','cookbook/default/no-revisions-W10_NCsLVyc-unsplash_e8rgom.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('34c1cf2c67f3','2024-06-23T12:55:07.666+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:07.666+00:00','Potato pottage with meatballs',0,'4-6 servings',10,35,replace('- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 1 tbsp sweet paprika powder\n- 1.5 kg (yellow) potato, peeled, diced\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tsp marjoram\n- 1 tbsp vinegar\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- salt, pepper, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n2. Add sweet paprika powder, stir for a little, then add diced potato to the pot. Pour water (broth is even better) over till it''s just covered. Add salt, pepper, marjoram and bay leaves, and cook until the potato soften, about 30 minutes.\n3. Add vinegar to the pot.\n4. Mix the sour cream with corn starch and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Slowly pour the mix to the potato and stir until thickens.\n5. Serve it with meatballs.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','cookbook/default/krumpli-fozelek_kfl5y9.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f3d59573344f5','2024-06-23T12:55:07.804+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:07.804+00:00','Pork stroganoff',0,'4 servings',10,80,replace('- 500 g pork fillet (shoulder)\n- 1 tbsp oil\n- 3 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 300 g mushroom\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 1 tbsp corn starch\n- 1 dl cream\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- salt, pepper, to taste\n- pickles, chopped, to taste\n- fresh parsley, chopped','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the pork fillet into thin strips, season it with salt and pepper.\n2. Heat a large pan, add a little oil, when it''s really hot add the meat. Stir fry it until brown.\n3. Add the garlic, stir in the mushrooms. On medium heat toss them for 5-10 minutes.\n4. Add bay leaves, water to almost cover and cook for 40-60 minutes until the meat softens.\n5. Mix cornstarch with cream and mustard. Add it to the pan with pickles, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened.\n6. Garnish with the parsley and serve with rice, noodles or macaroni pasta.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','cookbook/default/pork-stroganoff_g7dey0.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('44942f07002dd','2024-06-23T12:55:07.942+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:07.942+00:00','Lentil pottage (stew)',0,'4 servings',10,60,replace('- 400 g green lentil\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\n- 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped\n- 2 dried bay leaves\n- 1 tbsp mustard\n- 2 dl sour cream\n- 1 tbsp flour\n- 2 tsp sweet paprika powder\n- salt, to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour lentils in a large pot and cover them with cold water. Allow to soak for at least 4 hours. Then drain the water and give the lentils another quick rinse with fresh, cold water.\n2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent.\n3. Add lentils, bay leaves, mustard and salt to the pot. Add water to slightly cover. Cook for 60 minutes, until the lentils soften.\n4. Mix sour cream, sweet paprika, flour and 2 tbsp water together in a bowl, add this mixture to the pot to thiken the stew. After a short boil it is all done.','\n',char(10)),'','main dish','lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','cookbook/default/lencsefozelek_j0y1bm.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('b9eca41d5a8bb','2024-06-23T12:55:08.075+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:08.075+00:00','Crunchy baked potato',0,'3-4 servings',10,30,replace('- 1 kg potato, peeled, diced\n- salt, to taste\n- 1 tbsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp olive oil','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour diced potatoes in a pot with a little bit of salt and 1 tbsp of baking soda. Cook them for 8 minutes.\n2. Drain the water, add 1 tsp of olive oil to the potato. You can spice it up if you want (e.g. with rosemary), mix it well.\n3. Preheat the oven to 230 Celsius.\n4. Bake the potato for 30 minutes, turn them 1-2 times.','\n',char(10)),'','side dish','clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','cookbook/default/clark-douglas-37oYY2wHu0Q-unsplash_ccebso.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('e8e9102b23cb4','2024-06-23T12:55:08.209+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:08.209+00:00','Basic chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- berries for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Pour milk, chia seeds and optionally honey into a jar and mix well. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with berries or other fruits.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-anastasia-belousova-9022035_fhx418.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f8b8bd537a43b','2024-06-23T12:55:08.343+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:08.343+00:00','Vanilla & orange chia pudding',0,'1 serving',10,0,replace('- 1.5 tsp chia seeds\n- 100 ml milk of choice\n- vanilla extract\n- orange zest\n- a little honey or a half banana\n- orange slices for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a small jar, combine the milk, orange zest, and vanilla extract. Let settle for 2-3 minutes then mix again very well until you see no clumping.\n2. Cover the jar and store in fridge overnight or for at least 2 hours.\n3. Top with orange, drizzle with a little honey.','\n',char(10)),'This pudding will keep well in the fridge, covered, for about 5 days.','breakfast','pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','cookbook/default/pexels-alesia-kozik-6544212_tox2y3.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('99d16d130190f','2024-06-23T12:55:08.476+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:08.476+00:00','Basic tapioca pudding',0,'5 servings',10,35,replace('- 150 g small pearl tapioca\n- 700 ml coconut milk\n- vanilla extract\n- 1/2 tsp cinnamon\n- lime zest\n- berries or other fruits for topping','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Combine tapioca, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon in a pan on medium-high heat. Stir while bringing to a bare simmer.\n2. Lower the heat and cook uncovered, at the lowest possible heat, until the tapioca pearls have plumped up and thickened. Stir occasionally so the tapioca doesn''t stick to the bottom of the pan. (this take about 35 minutes)\n3. Pour into jars and place in the refrigerator overnight.\n4. Serve with sliced fresh fruit and lime zest.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','cookbook/default/tapioca-g09f6f5dfd_1920_go0sbz.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('56f3d06f34617','2024-06-23T12:55:08.611+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:08.611+00:00','Waffles a la mom',0,'4 servings',15,35,replace('- 120 g butter\n- whole 3 eggs\n- 140 g flour\n- 140 g sugar\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. In a large bowl mix flour, a pinch of salt, lemon zest and baking soda together.\n2. In a smaller bowl whisk butter with sugar, add the eggs one by one.\n3. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one.\n4. Preheat the waffle iron, brush with a little of oil.\n5. Cook waffles until golden brown and crisp.\n6. Serve immediately with maple syrup or fresh fruits.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','cookbook/default/mae-mu-dEUyLofZe5o-unsplash_tynk5z.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('c91b260c73f9e','2024-06-23T12:55:08.753+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:08.753+00:00','Eggplant dip',0,'2 jars',5,50,replace('- 2 eggplant\n- salt, pepper to taste','\n',char(10)),replace('\n1. Preheat the oven to 190 Celsius.\n2. Wash the eggplants, cut them half and place them on a baking sheet (cutted side on bottom). Poke some holes in the eggplants with a knife.\n3. Roast the eggplants for 45-50 minutes, turn them over at half time.\n4. Let them cool completely.\n5. Peel them with a knife. Make sure to remove any of the dark peel.\n6. Place the eggplants in a food processor with salt and pepper.\n7. Pour the dip into jars, keep them in the fridge.\n8. Serve with toasted bread, hard eggs and lots of veggies.','\n',char(10)),'You can experiment by adding 1 tbsp mayo or olive oil or dries tomatoes to the dip.','sauce','eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','cookbook/default/eggplant-dip_j046yt.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('a29f387aef03b','2024-06-23T12:55:10.225+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:10.225+00:00','Carrotcake cupcakes',0,'18 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 250 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 2 whole eggs\n- 3 carrot, peeled, shredded\n- 150 ml oil\n- 1 tsp cinnamon\n- 1 tsp clove\n- nutmeg\n- ginger to taste\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 100 g walnut/almond, chopped\n- orange zest\n\nCream Cheese icing:\n\n- 200 g cream cheese (mascarpone)\n- 3 tbsp powdered sugar\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, orange zest, spices, baking soda and nuts together.\n3. In another bowl mix the wet ingredients together: sugar, eggs, oil and shredded carrots.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nFrosting:\n\nCombine all icing ingredients until smooth and creamy. Spread over cooled muffins.','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','cookbook/default/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-4yTCqUHG1II-unsplash_iaui5p.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('327056b3e8fa5','2024-06-23T12:55:10.480+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:10.480+00:00','Double chocolate cupcakes',0,'20 cupcakes',15,20,replace('- 270 g flour\n- 75 g unsweetened cocoa powder\n- 250 g sugar\n- 1 whole egg\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 125 g butter\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- 100 g chocolate chips\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n\nWhite chocolate ganache:\n\n- 200 g white chocolate, roughly chopped\n- 100 ml cream\n- 1 vanilla bean','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, cocoa powder, baking soda and chocolate chips together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg, yogurt, vanilla extract and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)\n\nIcing:\n\n1. Fill a saucepan with some water and bring it to a very gentle simmer.\n2. Place a metal or glass bowl over the warm water but make sure it doesn''t actually touch the water. Pour the chocolate and cream into the bowl and stir frequently while it melts.\n3. Once all of the chocolate is almost completely melted, remove the bowl from the heat. The rest of the chocolate will continue to melt off-heat. \n4. Scrape the vanilla bean seeds by cutting down the center of the bean first and then scraping the seeds with the flat side of a knife. Add the vanilla bean seeds to the cream.\n5. Let it thicken as it cools. (30 min - 2 hours)','\n',char(10)),'Keep in the fridge for up to 5 days or frozen for up to 2 months.','dessert','dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','cookbook/default/dessy-dimcheva-Uc9HyrJMQdI-unsplash_md797f.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('9bf93c162c354','2024-06-23T12:55:10.711+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:10.711+00:00','Blueberry cupcakes',0,'12 cupcakes',10,20,replace('- 350 g flour\n- 200 g sugar\n- 3 whole eggs\n- 200 ml plain yogurt\n- 6 tbsp oil\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- pinch of salt\n- lemon zest\n- 1 tsp vanilla extract\n- 200 g blueberry','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, eggs, yogurt, vanilla extract and oil together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Fill each muffin cup with batter. Stud each muffin with blueberries.\n6. Bake them for 20-25 minutes. (toothpick test)','\n',char(10)),'','dessert','IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_20200703_175110_sq2upu.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('7a7c2fa7ea23c','2024-06-23T12:55:10.941+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:10.941+00:00','Chocolate-cranberry cookies',0,'35 cookies',10,13,replace('\n- 150 g flour\n- 50 g finely shredded coconut\n- 50 g dried cranberry\n- 100 g sugar\n- 100 g butter\n- 1 whole egg\n- 1 tsp baking powder\n- pich of salt','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.\n2. In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder, cranberry and shredded coconut together.\n3. In another bowl mix sugar, egg and butter together.\n4. Gently fold the wet mixture into the dry one. Stir them together.\n5. Roll the dough into balls (walnut size) place them on baking sheet well spaced apart. Flatten each slightly using your palm. (around 1 cm thick)\n6. Bake them for 13 minutes. (toothpick test)\n7. Let them cool on a wire rack.','\n',char(10)),'You can use nuts, other dried fruits, chocolate to vary the recipe.','dessert','DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','cookbook/default/DSC_0396_stdjfq.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('b22f76a7542b9','2024-06-23T12:55:11.332+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:11.332+00:00','Carrot soup with lentils and chorizo',0,'6 servings',10,30,replace('\n- 200 g chorizo\n- 500g carrots\n- 2 medium onions\n- 3 cloves of garlic\n- 2 red peppers\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 400 g canned peeled tomatoes\n- 0.5 tbsp cumin seed\n- 250 g dried red lentils\n- 1 chicken stock cube\n- 1.2 l boiling water\n- 8 tbsp yogurt greek style','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Cut the chorizo ​into 1 cm cubes. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat and fry the chorizo ​​for 8 minutes until it became crispy. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Do not clean the pan.\n2. Meanwhile, peel the carrots and cut them into 1 cm cubes. Chop the onion, finely chop the garlic. Clean the peppers and cut into 2 cm cubes.\n3. Bake the onion, carrots, bell pepper and cumin seeds for 10 minutes on medium heat in the pan with the chorizo ​​fat. Toss regularly. Add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Add the lentils, half the chorizo ​​and the peeled tomatoes. Crush the tomatoes against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add the water and crumble the stock cube over it. Bring the soup to a boil. Cook for 20-30 minutes with the lid on the pan, stir occasionally.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender, but not completely smooth. Season with pepper and salt.\n5. Serve the soup with the remaining chorizo ​​and yoghurt.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','cookbook/default/monika-grabkowska-_y6A9bhILkM-unsplash_wfavoi.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('80e0969167572','2024-06-23T12:55:11.693+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:11.693+00:00','Broccoli soup with croutons and cheese',0,'4 servings',10,25,replace('- 500 g broccoli\n- 2 tbsp oil\n- 4 cloves of garlic, finely chopped\n- 1 small onion, finely chopped\n- 0.5 tsp nutmeg\n- 500 ml water\n- 150 ml cream\n- salt, pepper\n- 1 tbsp flour or starch\n- shredded cheese','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Heat olive oil in a pan. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent. Add garlic and the broccoli florets. Pour in the half of the water, boil it and cook until the broccoli is tender. (You can use the stalks too, just peel them first!)\n2. Add the rest of the water, the dried herbs, and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\n3. Mix the cream with starch or flour and 1 tbsp water. Stir it until it gets smooth. Add the cream mixture to the soup, bring to a boil.\n4. Blend the soup with a stick blender. Serve with croutons and shredded cheese.','\n',char(10)),'','soup','megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','cookbook/default/megan-bucknall-qav5LFLbSUk-unsplash_vwzmzk.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('f2e6098053e1e','2024-06-23T12:55:12.082+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:12.082+00:00','Banana pancakes',0,'12 pancakes',10,30,replace('- 2 pieces of ripe banana\n- 2 eggs\n- 60 g sugar\n- 10 g vanilla sugar\n- 300 ml milk\n- 1 pinch of salt\n- 12 g baking powder\n- 220 g flour','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Smash the bananas with a fork, mix them with the eggs, sugar and vanilla sugar, then pour in the milk.\n2. Mix the salt, baking powder and flour, and add it to the banana mixture and whisk them together.\n3. Fry the pancakes in a non-stick pan, 2-3 minutes on each side.','\n',char(10)),'','breakfast','sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','cookbook/default/sara-cervera-WVgNJDjJFg0-unsplash_l8kxfb.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('941cf7cc34a3c','2024-06-23T12:55:12.213+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:12.213+00:00','Sourdough bread',0,'~800 g bread',700,40,replace('- 120 g sourdough starter\n- 470 g bread flour\n- 329 g water\n- 10 g salt','\n',char(10)),replace('Make the dough\n\n1. Feed 30 g sourdough starter with 60 g warm water and 60 g bread flour. (around 8-9 am) Let it rest for about 5-6 hours , until it''s active.\n2. Combine 120 g of the starter with water and bread flour. Knead for 10 minutes with hand or use a dough mixer. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 30 minutes.\n3. Add the salt to the dough and knead for 10 minutes or use the mixer.\n4. Every 30 minutes for the next 2 - 2 1/2 hours give your dough 3 - 4 stretches and folds\n5. After your stretch and folds are done, it is time for the bulk rise. Cover the dough with a led and let it rest for 2 hours.\n6. Shape the loaf, let bench rest for 15 minutes and then do one final shape. If you are adding flavor to your loaf, you will add it in during your the shaping.\n7. Place your shaped loaf into a banneton seam side up, cover with a plastic bag or wrap. Place in fridge to cold proof until next morning.\n\nBaking\n\n1. Preheat oven to 240˚C with a dutch oven inside.\n2. Place the loaf on parchment paper and score your loaf with a blade.\n3. Place it seam side down into the dutch oven with the parchment paper. Cover with lid and bake for 20 minutes.\n4. Remove lid and bake for another 20 minutes on 220 ˚C until the loaf is golden brown.\n5. Remove the loaf from the oven and let it cool on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.','\n',char(10)),'This is a 70% hydration sourdough bread recipe. The recipe is also very versatile and you can add seeds, nuts, herbs, spices, etc. to the dough.','bread','IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG_2222_ido2nm.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
INSERT INTO Recipe VALUES('994337ff73f5d','2024-06-23T12:55:12.347+00:00','2024-06-23T12:55:12.347+00:00','Pizza dough',0,'3x32cm pizza bases',90,30,replace('- 300 g warm water\n- 1 pinch of sugar\n- 15 g fresh yeast\n- 500 g 00 flour\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- 15 g salt\n- 2 tbsp sourdough starter, optional\n- corn flour for rolling','\n',char(10)),replace('1. Mix the water, sugar and yeast in a bowl and let it activate.\n2. Add the flour, olive oil and salt to the bowl with the yeast mixture and mix until a dough is formed.\n3. Let the dough rest for 1 hour, covered, in a warm place.\n4. Divide the dough into 3 equal parts and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.\n5. Preheat the oven to 250°C with the baking tray inside.\n6. Dust baking paper (for each pizza) with corn flour and roll out the dough into a 32 cm pizza base on it. Add your toppings.\n7. Bake them for 10 minutes at 250°C.','\n',char(10)),'','bread','IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','cookbook/default/IMG-2128_kdttzn.jpg','1f3f17330777c');
